name: maintenance, train, passenger, regional | maintenance, train, passenger, regional | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/9536/documentation

The dataset represents the maintenance of a regional train in Switzerland with a total weight of 171t and a life span of 40 years. ;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

Service starts with material expenditures for maintenance.

The dataset ends with the maintenance of one regional train. The dataset includes material consumption, transport, energy and fuel consumption, disposal and treatment.
category: C:Manufacturing/33:Repair and installation of machinery and equipment/331:Repair of fabricated metal products, machinery and equipment/3315:Repair of transport equipment, except motor vehicles

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data represents a train maintenance in Switzerland.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: For passenger transport equipment no SBB data has been available for the stationary energy and material consumption. Thus literature data is employed in this project. representing expenditures for one major revision (Maibach, 1999) as well as a regular substitution of break shoes (40 kg break shoes/car (Maibach, 1999). ;References:;Maibach M., Peter D. and Seiler B. (1999) Ökoinventar Transporte: Grundlagen für den ökologischen Vergleich von Transportsystemen und den Einbezug von Transportsystemen in Ökobilanzen. Technischer Schlussbericht. In: Schweizerischer Nationalfonds zur Förderung der wissenschaftlichen Forschung (ed. SPP Umwelt M.). 2nd Edition. INFRAS, Zürich
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The data of the material composition and energy consumption is based on literature studies.
